06/03/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Public Prosecutor Aleksandar Prcevski and Italy's anti-mafia prosecutor general, Pierro Luigi Vigna, sealed a protocol Friday (4 March) on co-operation in fighting organised crime.
The document envisions the exchange of information and expertise, as well as joint action and training.
Vigna described the level of new Macedonian legislation as high and in compliance with European standards, but said it must be fully and efficiently implemented.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 05/03/05;
A1 TV - 04/03/05)
